The paper discusses nonparametric statistical learning, which is a common topic in machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of distributed learning and random projections also suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses the use of kernel ridge regression, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence and may suggest that the paper belongs to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of random features may also suggest that the paper belongs to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
